            "text" : "Sent from my stepvda@mac.com.\n\nBegin forwarded message:\n\nFrom: itunesstoresupport@apple.com\nDate: 17 January 2021 at 11:52:55 CET\nTo: stepvda@me.com\nSubject: Re: Weird certificate error retrieving iTunes Match music on MacPro 3,1 el Capitan\nReply-To: itunesstoresupport@apple.com\n\nHi Stephane van der,\n\nThanks for keeping in touch and I would like to apologize for the delay of my response as I just came back from my rest day.\n\nNo worries, I found this troubleshooting steps to resolve the issue:\n\n&gt;In your Keychain under “login\" delete the VeriSign certificates and then quit and restart all browsers/itunes/app store.\n\nIn most cases, the above steps should resolve the issue. If the issue still persists, we may need you to contact our Technical Support Team to isolate the issue on their end as they have the expertise with this kind of issue: \n\nYou may reach them directly via this number:\n\n0800 80 407\n\nIf you’re currently out of the country, you can find the right number for your area on this page: \n\nhttps://t.co/KbdDyMMrDL  \n\nPlease know that my intention in referring you to our Technical Support Team is sincerely an attempt to be of help in the best possible way I can, and I do trust that they’ll assist you with the best of their abilities.  \n\nThanks,\n\nLara Flynn\nApple\n\n—————————— \n\nOn Jan 16, 2021, at 01:07 Stephane van der Aa &lt;stepvda@me.com&gt; wrote:\n\nHi Lara,\n\nHere’s an additional screenshot.\n\nI looked at the support note briefly, but I don’t see any solution to address certificate validation issues. I’ll have a detailed look later.\nCould it perhaps be possible that Root CA’s on el Capitan need to be updated?\n\nKind regards,\nStephane\n\nOn 15 Jan 2021, at 11:43, itunesstoresupport@apple.com wrote:\n\nHi Stephane,\n\nI wanted to send a follow-up note to see if all of your issues were addressed. \n\nI’ve copied my previous email for your reference.\n\nIf issue still persists, reply back with a screenshot of any error messages you’ve received. I’ll be happy to look into this further. \n\nThanks,\nLara Flynn\nApple\n\n-------------------- \n\nHi Stephane,\n\nThanks for contacting us. I understand that you’re receiving an error message with your songs. I’m happy to help you with this today.\n\nMost iTunes Match issues can be resolved by following the steps in this article:\n\nhttps://t.co/txHsy5qFhx\n\nIf the issues continue after following the steps in this article, reply back and i'll be happy to look into this further. Please make sure to include any specific error messages you’ve received.\n\nIf you have more questions about this issue, please reply to this email to let me know. I’m here to help.\n\nThanks,\n\nLara Flynn\nApple\n\nTM and copyright © 2021\nAll Rights Reserved / Privacy Policy / Support \n\nTM and copyright © 2021\nAll Rights Reserved / Privacy Policy / Support",
