            "recipientId" : "3309375033",
            "reactions" : [ ],
            "urls" : [ ],
            "text" : "in that case the problem is that you cannot fully turn auto-correct off in favor of the old user-manually-defined suggestions. I tried doing so when I encountered this problem on an iphone7 year ago or even longer. At that point I suspected a completed wrong keyboard and dependent config that could only have found its way to my previous phone if it were targeted for me, some kind off targeted hacking by very skilled hackers that have access to a lot of private data. This could have been around the time I filled a complained with police and court agains unknown. I provided detail on how Lastpass was hacked (despite 2FA) and subsequently several signs of illegal accesses happened in a short time span amongst others on iCloud. Moreover this was not limited to servers in a US jurisdiction. \nPlease if you can, get somebody in charge to hear me out before even more of our technology and internet becomes even less trustworthy. How many Colonial Pipeline and COOP ransomware cases need to happen before realizing this has all been going on under the radar of national security for way to long while victims remain unknown.",
